<link href="adcp.css" rel="stylesheet"><entry><xh5>straight off • straight out</xh5><p> <i>straight off</i>—(also: straight away) at once; without delay: The butler went <u>straight off</u> to Granny, and gave her notice; and she actually raised his wages, and prayed him to stop.</p><p> <i>straight out—</i>frankly; without reservation: I always know if he’s worried but he never tells me the details <u>straight out</u>. It sometimes slips out in conversation when the crisis is over.</p> </entry>
